next time how about a little coffee with 
the cremora 
state health officials were called in last weekend when a white 
powder coated cars and homes in this northern south carolina 
community but officials from the department of health and 
environmental control said there was nothing to worry about 
its just cremora said joe faris jr 
borden inc manufactures powdered coffee creamer and 
occasionally air vent driers inside the plant become clogged 
sending clouds of cremora drifting through the vents on the 
companys roof 
faris said bordens occasional accidents cause aesthetic 
problems 
but to the people who live and work near the plant the white 
powder is a source of aggravation 
the coffee creamer mixes with dirt and pollen and settles in a 
grimy layer over siding and windows residents complain when 
moistened by morning dew it hardens like concrete on car windows 
grace dover whose home is just a few yards from bordens back 
door said she has stood on her back porch and watched the creamer 
fall just like snowflakes 
on saturday she said the stacks out yonder were belching 
like a volcano 
bordens plant manager don seltz did not return telephone 
calls seeking comment 
