<TEXT>
a rare blood disorder linked to the recalled 
dietary supplement ltryptophan may be due to a natural chemical 
breakdown in the body rather than contamination researchers said 
the overthecounter healthfood supplement used to treat 
sleeplessness depression and other problems was pulled from store 
shelves last year after hundreds of people using it fell ill of 
eosinophiliamyalgia syndrome 
no contaminant has been found and natural chemical processes in 
the body during the breakdown of ltryptophan could be behind the 
painful blood disorder said the researchers at georgetown 
university medical center 
arguing against the contamination theory is that in spite of 
the fact that people have been searching for the contaminant it 
hasnt been identified said dr paul katz chief rheumatologist 
at georgetown 
also the ltryptophan implicated has been traced to three 
different manufacturers he said thursday from washington that 
argues a little bit against there being a commonsource 
contaminant 
ltryptophan is an amino acid a building block of protein 
found in many foods 
fourteen people who took ltryptophan have died in recent months 
and more than 1200 others have fallen ill with 
eosinophiliamyalgia which in milder cases causes aches rashes 
and fever 
a study of the problem by the georgetown researchers was 
published in todays journal of the american medical association 
katz and his colleagues believe ltryptophan supplements under 
certain conditions contribute to a buildup of serotonin a 
naturally occurring substance that helps nerves communicate with 
each other in the brain 
abnormally high levels of serotonin have been shown or suggested 
as factors in disorders similar to eosinophiliamyalgia syndrome 
the researchers said serotonin is a byproduct of the breakdown of 
ltryptophan 
katz said when you get away from the contamination theory 
which is still the leading theory people who develop this 
syndrome may have some intrinsic abnormality of ltryptophan 
metabolism 
the blood disorder may have occurred often in the past and 
diagnosed as something else katz said 
the number of people who have gotten this syndrome is 
relatively small compared to the number of people who take it 
ltryptophan katz said adding he could not estimate how many 
people have taken ltryptophan supplements sold for years over the 
counter 
the food and drug administration on nov 17 requested a 
voluntary recall of ltryptophan supplements and five days later 
extended the recall to include a ban on imports 
