<TEXT>
a dangerous game called elevator 
surfing blamed in the death of a college freshman has been a 
problem for years in highrise buildings officials say 
also called elevator action or piloting an elevator the 
hazardous sport involves climbing atop elevator cars either 
through trapdoors in the roof or by jamming doors open and riding 
on the roofs 
weve taken it terribly seriously weve been fighting it for 
a long time said val coleman public information director for 
the new york city housing authority 
coleman worked on a recently released cautionary videotape on 
the issue called children are too young to die there have been 
10 deaths and more than 50 injuries reported in new york during the 
past five years he said 
at the otis elevator co the largest elevator manufacturer in 
the united states officials have been concerned about the 
dangerous game for some time said michael jordanreilly spokesman 
for the hartford connbased company 
this is one of our major concerns he said 
susan beckett a student at the university of massachusetts 
told the campus newspaper the collegian that students ride atop 
elevators usually on the weekends when people are drunk 
at ms becketts school 18yearold joel mangion of newton was 
found dead sunday at the bottom of an elevator shaft friends said 
he had been jumping from one car to another in the double shaft 
about a year ago a student suffered serious injuries after 
falling 30 feet in an elevator shaft university officials said in 
the early 1970s a student died after riding in a chair tied to the 
bottom of an elevator car 
joseph zannini executive director of housing at the university 
said he has heard of the game occasionally during his 25 years in 
college administration 
theres so many unfortunate ways that young people sometimes 
lose their lives because they just dont think he said 
jordanreilly said the problem has probably existed as long as 
there have been elevators and as long as there have been people who 
want to try something dangerous 
in bridgeport conn police and firefighters spent two tense 
hours in january rescuing a 13yearold girl who was wedged between 
an elevator car and the shaft after she slipped and fell off the 
roof of the car in a public housing shelter police said the girl 
and her sister were playing on top of the elevator 
donald a robinson director of environmental health and safety 
for the massachusetts school said officials are looking for new 
ways to discourage elevator surfing 
the message needs to be made very clear how elevators should 
be used and not misused and to really emphasize the obvious 
significant consequences he said 
