contamination received 16 million of a 78 million court 
settlement for medical monitoring 
the federal agency wired the longawaited payment thursday to 
central trust co a cincinnati bank 
neighbors of the feed materials production plant about 18 miles 
northwest of cincinnati filed a 300 million lawsuit in 1985 
against the plants former operator national lead of ohio inc 
and its parent company nl industries 
the energy department as the fernald plants owner and contract 
employer of national lead negotiated a settlement approved last 
september by us district judge s arthur spiegel 
the energy department was to have paid the full 78 million by 
last oct 15 but didnt saying there was confusion over which of 
its budget accounts was to be used to provide the money 
the residents went back to spiegel and obtained an order to 
compel payment the judge had certified the lawsuit as a 
classaction on behalf of 14000 people living within five miles of 
the plant 
the energy department agreed to provide a second installment of 
205 million by the end of this year said stanley m chesley a 
lawyer for the neighbors the agency agreed to pay off the balance 
of the settlement with interest by the end of 1991 he said 
this is a true first in american history chesley said 
were finally going to get the medical monitoring the message 
is the judicial system works 
uranium processing for the governments nuclear weapons program 
was halted last july at the 39yearold plant 
