<TEXT>
when 12yearold michael thiel son 
of a top communist party official stood up for his father in 
school recently he was beaten up by classmates who broke his 
glasses 
it has been a long way down for the party that ruled east 
germany like a fiefdom for 40 years until its leaders were toppled 
by a popular rebellion in the fall 
there is a lot of hatred against the party and the children 
pick it up from their parents said michaels father frank 
deputy chief of the communist party in leipzig the city is an 
anticommunist stronghold where the protests that led to the 
nationwide movement began 
nearly 2 million party faithful have fled the party since the 
uprising the 600000 who remain have renamed themselves the party 
of democratic socialism and have frantically tried to convince 
voters before sundays election that they have moved from dogma to 
democracy 
we no longer want to shape man in the image of socialism we 
want to create a kind of socialism that man can live with said 
the 38yearold thiel a physics professor and party member for 20 
years 
but most east germans have had enough after four decades of 
secret police terror corruption travel restrictions and empty 
store shelves they are bitter about wasted lives in a drab society 
that squashed all individual ambitions 
we dont trust the communists anymore said andreas orlik a 
28yearold plumber from leipzig orlik stood in a crowd of 300000 
in the main karl marx square cheering west german chancellor 
helmut kohl and his promises of affluence for all in a united 
germany 
orlik said he would vote conservative in hopes that a 
freemarket economy will finally reward his hard work 
for the past eight years i have lived in a damp apartment with 
crumbling walls and they wouldnt even let me install a bathtub 
even though im a plumber orlik said i worked overtime for 
three years to buy a 17yearold car on the black market for 10000 
marks 1960 
the average monthly salary is 1100 marks about 215 
such sentiments are shared by many east germans the most 
optimistic forecasts say the revamped communist party will gain 
only 18 percent of the vote sunday 
party leaders are aware of their outcast status and acknowledged 
that they expect to be relegated to the political hinterlands 
a strong opposition for the disadvantaged read one campaign 
poster in leipzig 
thiel said the partys main objective in the new 400parliament 
would be to block a reunification plan under which east germany 
would agree to adopt west germanys constitution such a proposal 
is backed by the conservative alliance for germany a likely 
coalition partner in a new government 
we want to negotiate unification as a sovereign state and not 
simply be swallowed up by the west germans said thiel other 
leftist parties share this position but even they have refused to 
negotiate with the democratic socialists on a possible alliance in 
parliament 
the pds emerged from the communist party and therefore the 
other parties keep their distance said thiel he said his main 
reason for joining the communists as a teenager was to belong 
the party is not only being shunned in the political arena 
party members accustomed to a privileged life under the old 
regime now face widespread hostility and even violent attacks 
democratic socialist volunteers have been beaten up and windows of 
campaign headquarters have been smashed 
today i cant tell anybody that im in the party said 
mathias rulf a leipzig police officer patrolling in karl marx 
square he said he was one of just a few party members left in the 
once solidly communist police force 
these are lawless times muttered rulf in his 30s he 
watched the kohl supporters waving west german flags and streaming 
into the square for the rally 
party chief gregor gysi has warned of a new intolerance 
citing complaints by high school graduates that they are being 
barred from university because of party membership in the past 
party membership was a virtual prerequisite for admission to a 
university or job advancement 
amid this atmosphere of hostility the democratic socialists are 
trying hard to show voters they are no longer a party run by dour 
and dogmatic septuagenarians 
in a publicity stunt the 42yearold gysi performed a parachute 
jump the first in his life he quipped afterward you see from 
above how beautiful this country is and that there is no reason 
to just give it away 
the partys slogans are upbeat by east german standards 
borrowing freely from western commercials dont worry take 
gysi said one 
thiel claimed the changes are not just cosmetic most oldtime 
functionaries have quit or been fired since the peaceful revolution 
to make room for rankandfile members with new ideas he said but 
both thiel and the partys top candidate in leipzig dietmar 
keller were already functionaries under the old regime 
</TEXT>
