conference on nonprofit groups 
belyaeva one of 400 participants from around the world was 
referring the new growth of the voluntary third sector in her 
homeland where state economic power is diminishing and private 
industry encouraged 
belyaeva says her countrys fledging grassroots organizations 
must acquire western technical expertise in philanthropy how to 
raise funds how to organize how to network not necessarily 
western grants 
what our independent sector needs now is to learn how to 
fish she said during a panel discussion that included 
representatives from nonprofit sectors in west germany argentina 
australia and japan 
all eastern europeans are saying that said virginia a 
hodgkinson vice president of research for independent sector a 
10yearold nonprofit coalition of 650 corporate foundation and 
voluntary organizations which sponsored the conference 
it makes a whole lot of sense she said in an interview 
if you suppress the voluntary sector then only a certain few 
people develop those skills so what is necessary is to share 
experiences and to have experiences 
even for us groups long used to writing grant applications 
and staging yearly fundraising drives contact with the world 
nonprofit community is a very selfrenewing experience for all 
of us hodgkinson said 
