<TEXT>
president fernando collor de mello on 
friday implemented a sweeping emergency package of economic reforms 
that include a price freeze a new national currency and jail 
terms for economic crimes 
brazilians want serious action now said collor de mello as 
he announced his plans the new president took office thursday he 
is brazils first popularly elected leader in 29 years 
brazil has the developing worlds largest foreign debt 114 
billion inflation is 2700 percent and the budget deficit is 31 
billion millions of people live on the street or in shantytowns 
at the same time the country has the worlds eighthlargest 
economy and the western worlds thirdbiggest trade surplus 
collor de mello took office saying he would try to correct these 
imbalances 
the reform package takes effect immediately but must be approved 
by congress within 30 days if congress fails to vote collor de 
mello can reissue the measures for another 30 days 
under the emergency measures prices will be frozen 30 days and 
wages controlled inflation for march is expected to total 85 
percent but to help lower the rate workers will get a raise for 
the month equal to februarys inflation which was 73 percent 
on april 15 when the price freeze ends wages and prices will 
be prefixed by a governmentset amount tv globo brazils 
largest commercial network reported the salary and price hikes 
would be 40 percent in april and 20 percent in may 
the violence of inflation and runaway prices has made 
indispensable directed parameters for prices and salaries said 
collor de mello 
collor de mello said the measures would result in the 
weakening of speculation and the strengthening of investment 
the new conservative president also announced a new currency 
the cruzeiro which replaces the 14monthold new cruzado the 
cruzeiro is brazils fourth currency in as many years 
private economists said it would be created by lopping two zeros 
off the new cruzado which is now worth about 25 cents 
collor de mello declared a new law against economic abuses 
such as withholding goods from the market financial speculation 
and illegal price hikes 
who tries to cheat and fool the people will be jailed he 
said adding that store owners and managers found guilty of 
economic crimes will face fiveyear jail terms 
the most contoversial part of collor de mellos annoucement 
centered around his promise to balance the budget deficit this 
year promised new measures included 
major new taxes on the wealthy and on financial gains from 
trading in stocks and gold 
the suspension of 22 billion in annual federal subsidies to 
private enterprise that go to everyone from exporters to the 
computer industry 
an ambitious program of privatizations of stateowned 
companies brazil has 188 publicly owned firms many operate at a 
loss and they have total debts of about 62 billion 
stiff increases in public utility rates such as electricity 
and telephone 
firings of large numbers of brazils 700000 federal employees 
this years federal deficit will be zero theres no way to 
knock down inflation if the government spends more than it takes 
in collor de mello said 
collor de mello also said he wanted to integrate brazils 
economy into the world market eliminate import restrictions and 
bring foreign capital to the country 
we will modernize our economy and stimulate competition 
free initiative is the only way to sustained and progressive 
growth he said 
collor de mello signed laws thursday that reduced the number of 
government ministries from 25 to 12 and ordered the sale of 
governmentowned mansions and cars 
also decreed was the extinction of 24 federal agencies and 
companies including the brazilian institute of coffee which 
controls all coffee trade and the governments port authority 
portobras 
initial reactions to collor de mellos package were mixed 
weve worked all our lives for reforms like a balanced budget 
halelujah said rightwing senator jarbas passarinho of the 
social democracy party 
union leaders were mostly negative 
im still analyzing the package but my sensation is that 
workers have lost if he wants to take on the banks fine but 
weve got nothing else to give said luis antonio medeiros 
president of the powerful sao paulobased metalworkers union 
medeiros supported collor de mello in last years presidential 
campaign 
collor de mello was inaugurated for a fiveyear term thursday 
he replaced jose sarney who took office in an electoral college 
vote set up by the rightwing military regime that ruled brazil 
between 1964 and 1985 
