an earthquake shook the baja california 
city of la paz on friday rattling windows but apparently causing 
no injuries or damage residents said 
the tacubaya seismological station in mexico city said the quake 
measured 56 on the richter scale and was centered about 75 miles 
northeast of la paz 
it moved the tables everything moved the windows rattled it 
felt like something was hitting the house said alfonso sepulveda 
valenzuela we thought a car had hit a post 
but sepulveda and other residents said they saw no broken glass 
or other damage in downtown la paz the city is about 800 miles 
southeast of san diego 
jose alberto cesena private secretary to the mayor said no one 
in his office felt the quake and he heard no reports of it from 
other residents or local news media 
gonzalo carreno avitia a red cross employee in la paz said 
there were no calls about the quake 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph every increase of one whole number means a tenfold 
increase in magnitude an earthquake measuring five on the scale 
can cause considerable damage and one of six severe damage 
