ways and means committee looks a lot like what president bush 
campaigned on said robert mcintyre director of citizens for tax 
justice 
mcintyre whose organization has produced some widely read 
analyses of the tax system outlined what he said would be fairer 
way to reduce the deficit the central element in mcintyres plan 
would raise the top individual and corporate tax rates to 38 
percent up from 33 percent and 34 percent respectively 
sen daniel patrick moynihan dny also criticized 
rostenkowskis plan friday because it would continue to the use of 
surplus social security taxes to hide the real size of the overall 
federal deficit 
this is not government money moynihan said this money 
belongs to the contributors meaning the workers whose payroll 
taxes finance social security 
moynihan has proposed eliminating the surplus by cutting social 
security taxes 
moynihan also faulted rostenkowski for calling on retirees to 
give up their scheduled social security costofliving increase in 
1991 this is the first time i have heard such a proposal made 
from our democratic side on a unilateral basis moynihan said 
he said that although the freeze would be for only one year the 
failure to pay the increase would permanently reduce retirees 
benefits 
moynihans staff calculated that in 1991 the freeze would cost 
a typical couple retiring this year at age 65 about 588 over five 
years the loss would total 3192 
citizens for tax justice says rostenkowskis plan is flawed 
because its asking the wrong people to pay for the deficit 
the organizations substitute proposal would raise individual 
taxes by 139 billion over the next five years and corporate income 
taxes by 178 billion another 195 billion for deficit reduction 
would come from reducing the defense budget and 62 billion would 
be derived from cutting government interest payments 
all but the richest 5 percent of american families would 
fare better compared with rostenkowskis plan mcintyre said 
rostenkowski would eliminate the lingering deficit by 
eliminating costofliving raises for social security beneficiaries 
and recipients of many other government programs it would also 
raise income taxes on everybody who files a return with an 
especially big boost on the richest 600000 people and raise taxes 
on gasoline cigarettes wine and beer 
bush has said there is room for discussion in rostenkowskis 
