laws the companies are expected to face civil fines totaling 18 
million she said 
the committee chairman rep tom lantos dcalif called the 
operation a spectacular public relations extravaganza but said 
it had probably heightened the publics awareness about child labor 
violations 
lantos noted that the general accounting office congress 
investigative arm has reported that the 1000 federal labor law 
inspectors spend about 4 percent of their efforts on child labor 
investigations 
he called that percentage ludicrously and pathetically 
inadequate 
mrs dole has said she is not yet convinced additional resources 
are needed but said she will consider legislative changes such as 
stiffer penalties 
schumer and pease are drafting a bill that would increase the 
penalties and make other changes in the law such as expanding the 
definition of child labor violations to include doortodoor sales 
they expect to introduce the measure next month 
lantos said the panel will try to find out whether child labor 
violations have increased because of labor shortages or increased 
economic pressures on families 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

