by government analysts the planning department said friday 
the announcement was another indication that mexicos economy is 
pulling out of a protracted slump that began when world oil prices 
skidded in 1982 
this favorable result was accompanied by a reduction of 
inflation to nearly onethird that observed a year earlier the 
government news release said 
inflation in 1989 was 197 percent compared to 517 percent for 
1988 the bank of mexico reported 
the gross domestic product grew 29 percent in 1989 based on 
preliminary data from the national statistics geography and 
information institute the planning department said 
officials had forecast a 15 percent growth in the gdp for the 
year however president carlos salinas de gortari estimated in 
november at his first stateofthenation speech that 1989 growth 
would be 25 to 3 percent 
manufacturers including the countrys many factories dotting 
the 1950mile usmexico border were responsible for the 
increased 1989 output while farmers and ranchers forestry and 
fishing businesses produced less than in 1988 the statement said 
it blamed shrinkage in the other sectors on adverse climatic 
conditions 
growth in manufacturing was 6 percent while agricultural output 
fell 31 percent the department reported 
