exchange for a shareholder vote may 7 on splitting up the oil 
steel and gas company which he says would increase shareholder 
value 
other companies have thwarted proxy fights long before their 
annual meetings are held 
a year ago polaroid corp stopped a proxy attack by shamrock 
holdings inc by putting enough of its shares in friendly hands to 
defeat a shamrock slate of nominees shamrock gave up after the 
courts in delaware where polaroid is incorporated upheld the 
defensive move 
some other companies have averted proxy fights only by 
capitulating to dissidents demands 
