votes to unseat management in 1987 
coniston and the pilots wanted to replace the allegis board with 
directors who would sell the companys nonunited assets including 
westin hotels and hertz car rental the board ended up doing that 
anyway fired chairman richard ferris and changed the companys 
name to ual corp 
coniston later dropped its proxy campaign 
sometimes proxy battles that go to a vote do succeed on 
thursday the board of xtra corp a bostonbased trailer leasing 
concern said it had lost a proxy fight to a slate of dissidents 
who opposed managements plans to sell the company 
chartwell associates lp which includes the owners of mary kay 
cosmetics and a getty family trust plans a proxy battle for four 
seats on the 11member board of avon products 
the group which owns nearly 10 percent of stock in the cosmetic 
company said it wants to maximize shareholder value by selling 
avon which is best known for its core directsales business 
