minors who were injured and an estimated 59 killed in the 
workplace yet 37 employers who were cited for violations relating 
to those cases were fined a total of only 27000 he said 
the average penalty was a paltry 740 740 for a childs 
life in the united states schumer said 
the hearing came a day after labor secretary elizabeth dole 
announced that a threeday sting operation had uncovered 7000 
minors employed in dangerous jobs or working long hours in 
