<TEXT>
president fernando collor de mello today 
announced sweeping economic reforms including a 30day price freeze 
and a new currency to slash 2700 percent annual inflation and a 
31 billion budget deficit 
the austerity measures were announced one day after collor de 
mello was inaugurated as brazils first popularly elected president 
in 29 years 
the measures are profound courageous and indispensable 
society needs less state and more economy he said 
brazil has the western worlds eighthlargest economy and 
thirdbiggest trade surplus and is a producer and exporter of 
sophisticated goods such as computers cars aircraft and rockets 
but it also has third worlds largest foreign debt put at 114 
billion soaring inflation 7 million street children high adult 
illiteracy sprawling shantytowns epidemics of dengue malaria and 
yellow fever 
collor de mello said his freemarket economic reforms would move 
toward correcting brazils social and economic imbalances the 
measures introduced today included a crackdown on official 
corruption and whitecollar crime 
the reform package takes effect immediately but must be approved 
by congress within 30 days if congress fails to vote collor de 
mello can reissue the measures for another 30 days 
collor de mello said once the price freeze ends in midapril a 
government index will determine monthly wage and price increases 
globo brazils largest commercial television network said 
salaries and prices would jump 40 percent in april and 20 percent 
in may 
in march salaries will increase by februarys inflation rate 
or 73 percent inflation this month was expected to reach 85 
percent 
collor de mello also said the cruzado novo currency would be 
replaced by the cruzeiro the nations fourth currency in as 
many years will be devalued by about 100 percent versus the cruzado 
novo economists said 
the cruzeiro was the name of a currency suspended in 1986 
collor de mello decreed a new law to punish crimes against the 
economy including speculation and illegal price increases the law 
imposes a fiveyear prison term for violators whitecollar crime 
by public employees would also result in firings and jail time 
collor de mello said 
who tries to cheat and fool the people will be jailed 
collor de mello said 
the new measures included 
steep new income taxes for citizens and corporations 
the suspension of an estimated 22 billion spent annually in 
government subsidies to private enterprise export companies were 
the principal beneficiaries 
privatization of some of brazils 188 stateowned companies 
many of which operate at a loss they have total debts of around 
62 billion 
stiff increases in public utility rates 
an administrative reform that includes mass dismissal of public 
employees the federal government has about 700000 workers and 
aides to collor de mello have talked of firing about 80000 
the disbanding of some government enterprises including the 
