include jail time 
lehtinen said details of the planned restitution by general 
development were still under discussion and would not be official 
until he files a civil consent order 
under the agreement which still must be approved by financial 
institutions holding mortgages on general development homes up to 
100 million could be set aside for reimbursement 
lehtinen said federal officials hoped general development would 
remain in business but the plea agreement could require dismissal 
of other top executives 
general development is fighting to survive a cash shortage that 
the company says results from its legal problems lenders and 
investors have deserted general development since it disclosed that 
it might be indicted by a federal grand jury investigating how 
general development markets its homes 
