with commands from the ground 
engineers have succeeded in raising the orbit of an errant 150 
million communications satellite so that it wont crash through the 
atmosphere in the next nine days 
the higher orbit buys time for the owner intelsat to explore 
rescue options tony trujillo spokesman for the washingtonbased 
company said today that a letter was going to the national 
aeronautics and space administration discussing its help possibly 
a rescue by a space shuttle 
the satellite was left in an orbit that went within 1035 miles 
of earth after it failed to separate properly from its titan 3 
rocket after launch on wednesday if the satellite had remained at 
that altitude atmospheric drag would pull the spacecraft into the 
atmosphere where it would burn up 
using small steering thrusters and hydrazine fuel stored aboard 
for small course corrections engineers boosted the satellite to an 
eggshaped orbit of 161 miles by 276 miles a satisfactory position 
for parking 
this is very good news trujillo said of the successful 
effort to boost the 5ton satellite the maneuver does nothing 
however to restore the satellite to usefulness it must be in a 
geosynchronous orbit 22300 miles high to carry out its functions 
