properly from the second stage of its booster rocket the satellite 
was separated about seven hours later by computer commands sent 
from intelsats headquarters in washington 
but the rocket motor that was to have boosted the satellite into 
higher orbit remained attached to the second stage booster 
the titans second stage traveling at about the same speed as 
the satellite in the same elliptical orbit 90 to 190 miles above 
earth has until about wednesday before falling back to earth said 
