cents a gallon may lost 054 cent to 5289 cents and june dropped 
to 5232 cents down 063 cent 
analysts said demand for crude oil has weakened in recent weeks 
due mainly to seasonal factors including warmer weather nationwide 
and spring maintenance when refineries use less crude oil to make 
gasoline and other products 
