<TEXT>
bond prices shot up friday as traders detected 
weakness in the nations manufacturing sector and signs that the 
economy remains sluggish and inflation in check 
the treasurys benchmark 30year bond climbed 1316 point or 
813 per 1000 face amount its yield which rises when prices 
fall fell to about 854 percent from 861 percent late thursday 
the government released three reports on february economic 
statistics but analysts said figures showing of no change in 
wholesale prices and a 7 percent decline in housing starts during 
the month had little effect because of the influence of 
unseasonable weather 
instead bond prices climbed after the federal reserve said 
industrial production rose 06 percent less than economists had 
anticipated and largely due to a return of automobile workers after 
january slowdowns 
the factory sector of the economy remains weak said steven 
a wood economist with bankamerica capital markets in san 
francisco 
analysts had expected an increase in industrial production of 
08 percent to 09 percent wood said so the lower figure was 
interpreted as a further sign of weakness factoring in resurgent 
auto production the signs were even weaker he said 
what you had in the markets was expectations for worse news on 
the price front and the economic front which strengthened the 
credit market said maria fiorini ramirez president of ramirez 
capital consultants inc 
the industrial production report was good for the bond market 
because a slowdown in such economic indicators dampens the 
likelihood the fed will think it necessary to raise interest rates 
in order to curb inflation higher interest rates lower the value 
of existing bonds 
the labor departments producer price index showed no change 
following a huge 18 percent jump in january attributed to a 
holiday cold snap mild weather in february kept energy prices down 
economists said inflation which erodes the value of bonds 
still was on a 4 percent to 45 percent annual course 
also housing starts returned to a more normal pace in february 
declining 70 percent following a steep jump during januarys 
record warm weather 
analysts said both reports virtually were ignored by bond 
traders as they were in line with expectations 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
governments gained lsqb point to point intermediate maturities were 
up 1132 point to point and longterm issues shot up 2332 point 
to 1316 point according to telerate inc the financial 
information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer climbed 425 to 115181 
yields on threemonth treasury bills fell to 815 percent as the 
discount was down 2 basis points to 790 percent yields on 
sixmonth bills dropped to 826 percent as the discount was 2 basis 
points lower at 785 percent yields on oneyear bills were off 
sharply at 834 percent as the discount lost 5 basis points to 775 
percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest rate banks charge each 
other on overnight loans was quoted at 8 316 percent down from 
8 percent late thursday 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds closed at 91 1532 up 332 point the 
average yield to maturity was 749 percent compared with 748 
percent late thursday the bond buyer changed the mix of bonds in 
the index on friday 
